This option is for modifying the vertical alignment of a road centreline, by adding one or more vertical IPs (Intersection Points).  
On the [Icon: Road Tools button](images/centreline-tools-button.png) centreline tools toolbar in a longsection window, click the [Icon: Centreline Add IP button](images/tool-buttons/add-point.png) add point button.  
[Screenshot: centreline-add-vert-point-example.png - Example of adding a vertical point to a road centreline](images/centreline-add-vert-point-example.png)  
Select one of the straight sections between two existing vertical IPs (they will highlight as you move the mouse close).
Then position the new IP at the desired location.  
To place the points accurately, you can use the various *snap* options on the [snap toolbar](snap-tools.htm).  
Also, you can right-click the mouse to get a menu with additional options:  
[Screenshot: enter-chainage-level-menu.png - Right-click menu for adding new IP](images/enter-chainage-level-menu.png)

Site3D - Road and Site Design  
//<!--
show\_header('Vertical Curves');
show\_index();
//-->  
This option is for modifying the vertical alignment of a road centreline, by adding or modifying a vertical parabolic curve (filleting a vertical IP).  
On the [Icon: Road Tools button](images/centreline-tools-button.png) centreline tools toolbar in a longsection window, click the [Icon: Centreline Add IP button](images/tool-buttons/add-arc.png) add curve button.  
Select a vertical IP (they highlight as you move the mouse cursor around the longsection view).
Then move the mouse left/right to adjust the vertical curve length.  
[Screenshot: vertical-curve-example.png - Adding a Vertical Curve](images/vertical-curve-example.png)  
You will see the parabolic curve adjust as you move the mouse.
Click the mouse to place the vertical curve.  
[Screenshot: vertical-curve-example2.png - Vertical Curve Added](images/vertical-curve-example2.png)

