The Edit Junction Dimensions tool allows you to quickly modify the dimensions of a junction, or add a lane or taper to a junction.  
The [Screenshot: junction-dimensions.png](images/tool-buttons/junction-dimensions.png)**Edit Junction Dimensions** tool is found on the [Icon: Junction Tools button](images/junction-tools-button.png) junction tools toolbar.  
If you right click over the left or right side of a junction you will see the following menu:  
[Screenshot: junction-lane-taper-menu.png](images/junction-lane-taper-menu.png)  
Selecting either **Enter Radius** will allow you to input the radius of the closest junction fillet.  
Selecting either **Change to Taper** or **Change to Lane** will change the junction style.

