All proposed road networks must in some way connect to an existing road network. Connecting to an existing road in the form of a T-Junction is an important feature that can be easily designed in Site3D.  
This page describes the how to use Site3D's automated junction facility to connect your proposed road to an existing road on your topographical survey to precisely match the levels and grades:  
[Screenshot: junction-existing-road.png - Example of Junction with Existing Road](images/junction-existing-road.png)
[Screenshot: junction-existing-road-3d.png - 3D view of junction tying into survey surface.](images/junction-existing-road-3d.png)

