Site3D - Road and Site Design  
//<!--
show\_header('Custom DXF/DWG Export');
show\_index();
//-->  
When a design is exported to dwg/dwt the default layers from Site3D are used. A template (.dwt) file can be used to overwrite the layer colours and linetypes, and the block definitions.  
To change the layers names and colours shown in Site3D refer to [Custom Layer Names](custom-layer-names.htm)  
To get the layers and blocks required for the template file export a project to dwg/dxf which contains, every type of design item you will be using. Then, resave the file as a .dwt file. You can then customise this template using your CAD software of choice.

